  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Usefulness of non invasive ventilation in patients extubated after more than 48 hours of
      invasive ventilation is still in debate except for specific patients (chronic pulmonary
      disease and chronic heart failure).

      Many experimental and clinical studies have shown that diaphragmatic function is depressed by
      mechanical ventilation in intubated patients.

      The investigators will test the hypothesis that non invasive ventilation after extubation may
      improve diaphragmatic function
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
